{
  "info": {
    "name": "AutoTranslateAI API",
    "_postman_id": "a7e1c0d2-4b3a-4f7e-9c11-ataicollection01",
    "description": "End-to-end manual test flow for the AutoTranslateAI API.\n\nSetup:\n1. Rebuild + restart the Api/Worker (these endpoints are new).\n2. Postgres + RabbitMQ running; OpenAI__ApiKey and Azure Speech key configured.\n3. Postman > Settings > turn SSL certificate verification OFF (dev cert).\n4. Set the `baseUrl` variable (default https://localhost:7269).\n\nEnums in bodies are integers: voiceGender 0=Female 1=Male; subtitleMode 0=None 1=Hardsub 2=Softsub; bgmMode 0=DemucsAI 1=Duck(-12dB) 2=None.\n\nRun folders in order. Requests capture jobId/segmentId/proposalId into collection variables automatically. Status endpoints are polled by re-sending until the status matches.\n\nPhase 5: segment update + bulk accept speakerLabel + assignedVoice (multi-speaker) — pick voice ids from GET /api/voices?language=... . Logo watermark is configured in appsettings (\"Logo\": { Path, Position, ScalePercent, Margin }), not via the API.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
